      "message": "Line 730: 🟡 Suggestions - The new clickable indicators are implemented with nested `RowLayout`/`Text` plus `TapHandler`, but there is no accessible name/role or keyboard activation path. This makes the edit history and original/modified toggle mouse-only. Use a `Button`/`LabelButton` pattern used elsewhere in the app, or add accessibility metadata and key handling.\n```suggestion\nAccessible.role: Accessible.Button\nAccessible.name: root.showOriginal ? JamiStrings.showModifiedMessage : JamiStrings.showOriginalMessage\nKeys.onReturnPressed: root.showOriginal \u003d !root.showOriginal\nKeys.onSpacePressed: root.showOriginal \u003d !root.showOriginal\n```",
